1
00:01:08,920 --> 00:01:09,400
Brother

2
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:14,000
Brother

3
00:01:22,120 --> 00:01:22,920
Don't cry.

4
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:28,440
You should be

5
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:30,040
happy for me.

6
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:34,360
Because I'll soon

7
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:37,640
be able to see our parents.

8
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:45,080
It's been so many years.

9
00:01:47,720 --> 00:01:49,080
I really miss them.

10
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:50,160
Brother.

11
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:54,440
From now on,

12
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:57,640
I won't be able to stay by your side.

13
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:02,800
Take good care of yourself.

14
00:02:04,880 --> 00:02:05,200
Brother.

15
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:07,520
You're not a kid anymore.

16
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:09,760
Find a good family

17
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,160
and get married.

18
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:14,680
Don't worry.

19
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:18,440
If he dares to bully you,

20
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:23,040
I won't let him off even as a ghost.

21
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:27,680
Brother.

22
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:47,160
I'm leaving.

23
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:49,080
No.

24
00:02:49,320 --> 00:02:50,600
Don't leave me behind.

25
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:52,320
Let's go.

26
00:02:56,440 --> 00:02:56,880
Brother!

27
00:02:57,880 --> 00:02:58,520
Brother!

28
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:01,160
Brother!

29
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:03,800
In the next life,

30
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:07,240
let's be siblings again.

31
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:25,440
Brother!

32
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:11,600
Excuse me.

33
00:04:12,040 --> 00:04:12,600
Excuse me.

34
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:13,840
Inspector.

35
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:14,640
The Marshal...

36
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:15,480
Something happened to him.

37
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:40,720
Dad!

38
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,040
Dad!

39
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:48,880
Impossible.

40
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:51,160
Impossible.

41
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:52,600
It's impossible.

42
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:54,880
Impossible.

43
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:58,320
Jinrong.

44
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:00,320
Jinrong.

45
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:08,560
Help the Inspector out first.

46
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:09,600
Leave this to me.

47
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:10,640
Let's go.

48
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:11,600
Let's go.

49
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:35,560
Dad!

50
00:05:45,080 --> 00:05:45,840
Dad!

51
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,160
I heard Marshal Huang died

52
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:52,920
under very bizarre circumstances.

53
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:54,160
The way he looked...

54
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:55,760
It was simply too gruesome to look at.

55
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:59,760
Back in the day, Marshal Huang in our Jiangyu City

56
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,360
was a man whose word was law.

57
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:03,240
To end up like this now...

58
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,800
It really makes you sigh.

59
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:07,480
I have a cousin

60
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:08,760
who works at the Marshal's Residence.

61
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,120
A few nights ago,

62
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:11,920
he vaguely saw a dark shadow

63
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:13,360
from inside the garden

64
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:14,320
flash past.

65
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:16,000
That figure was so elusive,

66
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:18,000
it didn't seem human at all.

67
00:06:18,760 --> 00:06:19,800
It looked like an evil spirit.

68
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,000
An evil spirit?

69
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:23,160
What should we do then?

70
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:24,480
Will this evil spirit

71
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,360
come after us too?

72
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:27,600
Just hearing about it

73
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:28,600
makes me scared.

74
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:10,880
Stop drinking.

75
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:16,480
These past few days,

76
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,040
you've been drinking constantly.

77
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,040
Not eating anything,

78
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:23,560
how can your body take it?

79
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:31,000
Your father's autopsy report

80
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:33,160
is out.

81
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:57,440
Marshal

82
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:59,000
His eyes are bulging,

83
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:01,480
and his eyes

84
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:02,760
are bloodshot.

85
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:05,000
He bled from all seven facial orifices.

86
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,800
The Marshal's hands were tightly clutching his throat,

87
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:09,480
with his fingers digging deep into the flesh.

88
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,000
The preliminary conclusion

89
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:13,360
is that the Marshal's cause of death

90
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,320
is self-strangulation,

91
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:17,680
resulting in asphyxiation.

92
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:21,240
Yes.

93
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,120
My father

94
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,440
couldn't have committed suicide.

95
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,560
Given human survival instincts,

96
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:29,240
a person

97
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:30,000
could not possibly

98
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,000
use that much force

99
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,000
to strangle themselves to death.

100
00:08:32,920 --> 00:08:33,680
It seems the killer

101
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:34,880
is extremely ruthless

102
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:36,880
and incredibly strong.

103
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:38,360
It's him.

104
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:41,560
It must be him again.

105
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:45,800
No matter who it is,

106
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,560
I will definitely catch him this time.

107
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:50,760
Chuncheng,

108
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,240
is there any other evidence at the scene?

109
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:54,240
Inside the warehouse,

110
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:56,120
there are no obvious signs of a struggle.

111
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:57,600
The Marshal

112
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:58,480
seems to have been

113
00:08:58,480 --> 00:08:59,680
caught completely off guard

114
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:00,920
when he was murdered.

115
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:01,920
So,

116
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:03,560
my father

117
00:09:03,560 --> 00:09:05,000
must have also known the killer.

118
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:07,680
What do you mean "also known the killer"?

119
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:13,680
"This time"?

120
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:16,760
What other time was there?

121
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,920
The things you two are saying today,

122
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,480
I don't understand any of it.

123
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:28,360
Who exactly is this person they both knew,

124
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:32,160
but I don't know about?

125
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:33,560
"They"?

126
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:37,520
Who else?

127
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:43,120
Are you hiding something from me?

128
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,720
Is there something

129
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,360
that I'm not allowed to know?

130
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:58,840
Even now,

131
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,520
are you still unwilling

132
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:03,880
to tell me the truth?

133
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:10,640
Huang Jinrong,

134
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,480
even at this point,

135
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:15,000
you still refuse to say anything.

136
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:17,000
I, Duan Qingqing,

137
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,760
ended up like this today

138
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:21,960
precisely because you refuse to say anything.

139
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:28,600
A year ago,

140
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:31,480
at our wedding,

141
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:34,120
in front of everyone,

142
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,360
you suddenly left,

143
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:38,120
making me the laughingstock of the whole city.

144
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,360
Is the groom unwilling?

145
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:52,120
Why did he leave?

146
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:53,520
Why did the groom run away?

147
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:54,760
You can't just do that!

148
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:01,760
Father!

149
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:04,000
Father!

150
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:06,000
Father!

151
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:07,760
Father!

152
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:10,600
My father

153
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:14,480
was so furious he had a heart attack on the spot

154
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,720
and passed away suddenly.

155
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:21,880
Our Duan family

156
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:25,000
has been in decline ever since.

157
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,120
But what about you?

158
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,960
Even now,

159
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:33,000
you haven't offered a single word of explanation.

160
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:38,880
Since that's the case,

161
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:44,000
from now on,

162
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:47,200
we will go our separate ways completely.
